Class RagialQueryMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ragialquery.data.RagialQueryMatcher

  • public class RagialQueryMatcher
extends java.lang.Object
    The class that handles the queries to Ragial.com and also prepares RagialData and its VendingNow list for use.

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<RagialData[]> searchRagial(java.lang.String name)

        Returns:

      • searchRagialSpecificly

        public RagialData searchRagialSpecificly(java.lang.String exactName)
        Ensures that only one correct result will be returned for a given name. It must be run on a different thread since it has a blocking call to the ExecuterService.
        Parameters:
        exactName - - The exact name, word for word, character for character of the item to be searched
        Returns:
        RagialData - Forces only one correct result to be returned from the array. If data is not found, returns null

      • searchRagialSpecificly

        public static RagialData searchRagialSpecificly(java.lang.String exactName,
                                                RagialData[] datas)
        Helper method for cases when RagialData[] is already available from prior call. Merely finds the specific item, or returns null.
        Parameters:
        exactName - - The exact name, word for word, character for character of the item to be searched
        datas - - A RagialData[] obtained from a prior call.
        Returns:
        RagialData - forces only one correct result to be returned from the array. If data is not found, returns null.

      • getOnSaleItems

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<java.util.ArrayList<RagialData.VendingNow>> getOnSaleItems(java.lang.String name,
                                                                                              RagialData[] datas)

        datas - - RagialData[] obtained from a prior call.

      • getOnSaleItems

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<java.util.ArrayList<RagialData.VendingNow>> getOnSaleItems(java.lang.String name,
                                                                                              RagialData[] datas,
                                                                                              boolean checkOverLongTermAsWell)
        Calculates and returns a list of VendingNow items which satisfy the criteria that all items on this list must have a price lower than the average in the short term (and long term as well, if checkOverLongTerm = true). ie : The item is on sale.
        Parameters:
        name - - Name of the item to be checked if it is on sale.
        datas - - RagialData[] obtained from a prior call.
        checkOverLongTermAsWell - - A boolean to request checking over long term prices as well.
        Returns:
        A Future of an ArrayList of VendingNow items - List of items that are on sale in the long term.

      • getOnSaleItems

                                                                                              RagialData datas,
                                                                                              boolean checkOverLongTermAsWell)
        Calculates and returns a list of VendingNow items which satisfy the criteria that all items on this list must have a price lower than the average in the short term (and long term as well, if checkOverLongTerm = true). eg : The item is on sale.

      • destroyExecutor

        public boolean destroyExecutor()
        ExecutorService needs to be killed or it will run forever. Do not forget to call this method! Kills both its object as well as shutdowns all executing threads.
        Returns:
        true if executor was running and is now shutdown. False if already shutdown.

      • isExecutorAvailable

        public static boolean isExecutorAvailable()
        Use this to check if a query can be made on Ragial.com with the ExecutorService
        Returns:
        true if Executor is available, else return false.

      • finalize

        protected void finalize()
                 throws java.lang.Throwable
        Ensures that the ExecutorService is destroyed when the RagialQueryMatcher object is killed. This is only a fail safe method. It is still recommended to manually shutdown the executor service with destroyExecutor()
        Overrides:
        finalize in class java.lang.Object
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
